<subSubSection id="90557B3B0FD88995DC560F06261B9EED" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" type="description">
<paragraph id="AA3D9F3D2B13734FB3642588061AB68E" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<emphasis id="44BB5E184A3830C18F769518E0697554" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
H. 
<taxonomicName id="1EB02B969FF3F83A92F4925821EE845C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pilosella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="590" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pilosella</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(Nr. 4a) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="10FC5E66A59DB71FB0E7007B6647DABA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<normalizedToken id="F1B3B0CF6625CC37F94151D895EF9A94" originalValue="Hülle" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Huelle</normalizedToken>
7
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="A70290AAE2F00ED8157EEF722747296F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
10 mm lang; 
<normalizedToken id="A8DBDF9D1EE5F3A9BD5FB48358626D89" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
ohne 
<normalizedToken id="2BE53EA5E92043F55AD5E94558B0C24D" originalValue="Drüsenhaare" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Druesenhaare</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="534B8263760DC8B72B538E8162E2A62E" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Bluete</normalizedToken>
; Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="126377B932D77ECFEC2CB9A0B89A5C8E" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="DA45B2AE0474662286AA37404ACEBE69" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CACFBBAB50BEC17F3FFEA89B9AE83CEB" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="E1B29182C559A996A849D6290A0AA937" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. Trockene, steinige, oft kalkreiche, tonige 
<normalizedToken id="8D7620CECD5C2958E34700615D0CACF9" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in warmen Lagen. Trockenrasen, Felsensteppen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DA4039F0BF3B689EC6E8D7AB50BFF8D" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="C476968EFF85BD63278191839DA74BD2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="41C4329826012291E5E8544B1B466AFD" originalValue="Westalpin-pyrenäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Westalpin-pyrenaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="DA082564985E12DC885626E4D4FA10F8" originalValue="Pyrenäen" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Pyrenaeen</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="EFB7D3DA187E344E8B8190B08EE34724" originalValue="Corbières" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Corbieres</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="70414D27F9F450B81E021A552B261A89" originalValue="Südfrankreich" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Suedfrankreich</normalizedToken>
, West- und 
<normalizedToken id="497A76932361DDCAD49BC2FF50D1B2D5" originalValue="Südalpen" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Suedalpen</normalizedToken>
(
<normalizedToken id="4744E2CAA3695B2DB16F7ACAA94C9FA7" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Oberwallis und Belluno in den Venetischen Alpen), Ligurien, 
<normalizedToken id="0CAC597CF9735B63FA03D3405E298A0D" originalValue="südlicher" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">suedlicher</normalizedToken>
Jura. - Im Gebiet: 
<normalizedToken id="56E90E743FB2303B46FC753D2275A034" originalValue="Südlicher" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Suedlicher</normalizedToken>
Jura (
<normalizedToken id="5BD38988D936A03BCFF8D1B79BE001AB" originalValue="nordostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">nordostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Lignerolles in der Waadt), westliche Alpen (Gegend von 
<normalizedToken id="E0DB4B0523EDBE3E3500F12971542AC6" originalValue="Chambéry" pageId="null" pageNumber="590">Chambery</normalizedToken>
in Savoyen, im Wallis von Martigny bis Gerental, Aostatal, Valsesia); ziemlich selten.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
